COMMENT ON TABLE ppdm.sf_rig
    IS 'SUPPORT FACILITY RIG: The equipment that is used to drill a wellbore. In onshore operations, the rig is situated on a stable drilling pad, and includes the equipment used the drill the wellbore and the equipment necessary to support it, such as mud tanks, drawworks, masts and rotary table. Offshore rigs include the same main components as onshore rigs, but are situated on a vessel of drilling platform, and are configured to allow the drilling apparatus to pass through water before drilling into the earths surface.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.sf_subtype
    IS 'SUPPORT FACILITY SUBTYPE: The type of support facility that is described by this row of data. These values are managed by check constraint, and may only be the name of a valid sub type of support facility.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_id
    IS 'RIG IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier assigned to the rig. Rigs may be drilling rigs or other kinds of service rigs assigned to a well site.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.active_ind
    IS 'ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently either active / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.boiler_manufacturer
    IS 'BOILER MANUFACTURER: Unvalidated column for the manufacturer information for the boiler. For validated manufacturer information, go to the EQUIPMENT tables.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.boiler_power
    IS 'BOILDER POWER: Power rating for the boiler.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.boiler_power_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.choke_manifold_press
    IS 'CHOKE MANIFOLD PRESSURE: A set of high-pressure valves and associated piping that usually includes at least two adjustable chokes, arranged such that one adjustable choke may be isolated and taken out of service for repair and refurbishment while well flow is directed through the other one. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.choke_manifold_press_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.choke_manifold_size
    IS 'CHOKE MANIFOLD SIZE: A set of high-pressure valves and associated piping that usually includes at least two adjustable chokes, arranged such that one adjustable choke may be isolated and taken out of service for repair and refurbishment while well flow is directed through the other one. (Schlumerger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.choke_manifold_size_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.clear_work_height
    IS 'CLEAR WORKING HEIGHT: the amount of clear working height space on the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.clear_work_height_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.commission_date
    IS 'COMMISSION DATE: The date that the rig was put into commission.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.decommission_date
    IS 'DECOMMISSION DATE: The date that the rig was decommissioned.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.desander_type
    IS 'DESANDER TYPE:A hydrocyclone device that removes large drill solids from the whole mud system. The desander should be located downstream of the shale shakers and degassers, but before the desilters or mud cleaners. A volume of mud is pumped into the wide upper section of the hydrocylone at an angle roughly tangent to its circumference. As the mud flows around and gradually down the inside of the cone shape, solids are separated from the liquid by centrifugal forces. The solids continue around and down until they exit the bottom of the hydrocyclone (along with small amounts of liquid) and are discarded. The cleaner and lighter density liquid mud travels up through a vortex in the center of the hydrocyclone, exits through piping at the top of the hydrocyclone and is then routed to the mud tanks and the next mud-cleaning device, usually a desilter. Various size desander and desilter cones are functionally identical, with the size of the cone determining the size of particles the device removes from the mud system. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.desilter_type
    IS 'DESILTER TYPE: A hydrocyclone much like a desander except that its design incorporates a greater number of smaller cones. As with the desander, its purpose is to remove unwanted solids from the mud system. The smaller cones allow the desilter to efficiently remove smaller diameter drill solids than a desander does. For that reason, the desilter is located downstream from the desander in the surface mud system. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.drawworks_type
    IS 'DRAWWORKS TYPE: The machine on the rig consisting of a large-diameter steel spool, brakes, a power source and assorted auxiliary devices. The primary function of the drawworks is to reel out and reel in the drilling line, a large diameter wire rope, in acontrolled fashion. The drilling line is reeled over the crown block and traveling block to gain mechanical advantage in a "block and tackle" or "pulley" fashion. This reeling out and in of the drilling line causes the traveling block, and whatever may be hanging underneath it, to be lowered into or raised out of the wellbore. The reeling out of the drilling line is powered by gravity and reeling in by an electric motor or diesel engine.(Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary). A link to the specific piece of equipment that has been used may be captured in the table SF EQUIPMENT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.effective_date
    IS 'EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.expiry_date
    IS 'EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.hookblock_rating
    IS 'HOOKBLOCK RATING: The rating for the hookblock, as the amount of force it is rated for.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.hookblock_rating_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.hookblock_type
    IS 'HOOK or HOOKBLOCK TYPE: The high-capacity J-shaped equipment used to hang various other equipment, particularly the swivel and kelly, the elevator bails or topdrive units. The hook is attached to the bottom of the traveling block and provides a way to pick up heavy loads with the traveling block. The hook is either locked (the normal condition) or free to rotate, so that it may be mated or decoupled with items positioned around the rig floor, not limited to a single direction. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.hook_load_capacity
    IS 'HOOK LOAD CAPACITY: The maximum hook load rated for this rig. Hook load is the total force pulling down on the hook. This total force includes the weight of the drillstring in air, the drill collars and any ancillary equipment, reduced by any force that tends to reduce that weight. Some forces that might reduce the weight include friction along the wellbore wall (especially in deviated wells) and, importantly, buoyant forces on the drillstring caused by its immersion in drilling fluid. If the BOPs are closed, any pressure in the wellbore acting on the cross-sectional area of the drillstring in the BOPs will also exert an upward force. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.hook_load_capacity_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.kb_ground_dist
    IS 'KELLY BUSHING TO GROUND DISTANCE: the distance from the kelly bushing to the ground on the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.kb_ground_dist_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mast_height
    IS 'MAST HEIGHT:  The height of the mast.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mast_height_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mast_type
    IS 'MAST TYPE: The structure used to support the crown blocks and the drillstring. Masts are usually rectangular or trapezoidal in shape and offer a very good stiffness, important to land rigs whose mast is laid down when the rig is moved. They suffer from being heavier than conventional derricks and consequently are not usually found in offshore environments, where weight is more of a concern than in land operations. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary). In order to capture a relationship to a specific piece of equipment or the manufacturer of the equipment,please use SF EQUIPMENT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.max_depth
    IS 'MAXIMUM DEPTH: The maximum depth that the rig is able to drill to.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.max_depth_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mud_tank_count
    IS 'MUD TANK COUNT: The number of mud tanks for the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mud_tank_size
    IS 'MUD TANK SIZE: The size of the mud tanks on the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.mud_tank_size_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.operator_ba_id
    IS 'OPERATOR BUSINESS ASSOCIATE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the business associate who operates the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.owner_ba_id
    IS 'OWNER BUSINESS ASSOCIATE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the business associate who owns the rig. Note that partner shares can be handled through the INTEREST SET module, via the foreign key in SF COMPONENT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.ppdm_guid
    IS 'ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global unique identifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used, optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the data model DDL should be created.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.remark
    IS 'REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_category
    IS 'RIG CATEGORY: The category of the rig, describing its basic purpose. Typical examples include drilling rig, service rig, wireline rig, workover rig, rathole rig etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_class
    IS 'RIG CLASS: Indicates the class of rig, such as single, super single, double, triple.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_code
    IS 'RIG CODE: This reference table defines the unique codes assigned to each rig or installation. For example, the code "GA" may be assigned to the drilling rig Glomar Arctic III.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_name
    IS 'RIG NAME: Full name of the rig. Usually denormalized from the table SF ALIAS, based on the PREFERRED IND flag.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rig_type
    IS 'RIG TYPE: A reference table describing the type of rig installation. For example land, barge, submersible, platform, jackup, drillship, semisub or artificial island.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rotary_table_cap
    IS 'ROTARY TABLE CAPACITY: the carrying capacity of the rotary table, often in tons.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rotary_table_cap_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rotary_table_size
    IS 'ROTARY TABLE SIZE: The revolving or spinning section of the drillfloor that provides power to turn the drillstring in a clockwise direction (as viewed from above). The rotary motion and power are transmitted through the kelly bushing and the kelly to the drillstring. When the drillstring is rotating, the drilling crew commonly describes the operation as simply, "rotating to the right," "turning to the right," or, "rotating on bottom." Almost all rigs today have a rotary table, either as primary or backup system for rotating the drillstring. Topdrive technology, which allows continuous rotation of the drillstring, has replaced the rotary table in certain operations. A few rigs are being built today with topdrive systems only, and lack the traditional kelly system. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.rotary_table_size_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.source
    IS 'SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as the source of information for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.substructure_type
    IS 'SUBSTRUCTURE: Foundation on which the derrick and engines sit. Contains space for storage and well control equipment. (http://www.oilonline.com/info/glossary.asp). For details about specific equipment used or manufacturers, please use the SF EQUIPMENTtable.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.substruct_casing_cap
    IS 'SUBSTRUCTURE CASING CAPACITY: The maximum capacity of the substructure to hold casings removed from the well bore, including those that are hung from the overhead equjpment.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.substruct_casing_cap_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.substruct_setback_cap
    IS 'SUSTRUCTURE SET BACK CAPACITY: The amount of force the substructure can handle as wieght on the derrick and rack in addition to the normal rig equipment.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.substruct_setback_cap_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.swivel_rating
    IS 'SWIVEL RATING: The rating for the swivel, usually the weight it is able to hold. The swivel is a rotary device hanging from the hook and the travellling block. Its function is to allow the drill stem to rotate freely from the apparatus.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.swivel_rating_ouom
    IS 'SWIVEL RATING ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE: The units of measure in which the swivel rating was originally received.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.swivel_type
    IS 'SWIVEL TYPE: A mechanical device that must simultaneously suspend the weight of the drillstring, provide for rotation of the drillstring beneath it while keeping the upper portion stationary, and permit high-volume flow of high-pressure drilling mud from the fixed portion to the rotating portion without leaking. (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.top_drive_model
    IS 'TOP DRIVE MODEL: unvalidated information about the make and model of the top drive. In order to validate this information, please use SF EQUIPMENT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.top_drive_rating
    IS 'TOP DRIVE RATING: the rating for the top drive. The top drive is used to rotate the drill stem, and may be used in place of the rotary table. The top drive may include the swivel, elevator, tongs and hook.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.top_drive_rating_ouom
    IS 'TOP DRIVE RATING ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE: The units of measure in which the top drive rating was originally received.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.water_depth_capacity
    IS 'WATER DEPTH CAPACITY: Depth of the water that the rig can operate in.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.water_depth_datum
    IS 'WATER DEPTH DATUM: Identifies the point near or on the rig from where the water depths are to be measured.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.water_depth_ouom
    IS 'WATER DEPTH OUOM: Water depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.working_pressure
    IS 'WORKING PRESSURE: The working pressure for the rig.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.working_pressure_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_changed_by
    IS 'ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_changed_date
    IS 'ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_created_by
    IS 'ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_created_date
    IS 'ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_effective_date
    IS 'ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was made available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.sf_rig.row_expiry_date
