COMMENT ON TABLE ppdm.well
    IS 'WELL: A table for general and header information about a well. A well is an actual or proposed hole in the ground, designed to exchange fluids between a subsurface reservoir and the surface (or another reservoir) or to enable the detection and measurement of rock properties. A wellbore is a cylindrical hole created by a drill. A well may consist of zero, one, or more wellbores. Their relationships are described by the table WELL_XREF. Information from other well tables (e.g. key dates and depths) may be included (denormalized) for convenience. The term "well" is used in the column name and comments to mean "well", "wellbore", either, or both (depending on the context). The column WELL_LEVEL_TYPE is used to describe which type exists in a row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.uwi
    IS 'UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as the primary key for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.abandonment_date
    IS 'ABANDONMENT DATE: Date the well was plugged and permanently abandoned.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.active_ind
    IS 'ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently either active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.area_id
    IS 'AREA ID: Unique identifier for any named area such as a country, province, project area, area of interest, offshore area, district etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.area_type
    IS 'AREA TYPE: Unique identifier for the type of area, such as country, state, AOI etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.assigned_field
    IS 'ASSIGNED FIELD: The field that this well is assigned to for production purposes.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.base_depth
    IS 'BASE DEPTH: the deepest, bottom or base measured depth in which this well component is found.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.base_depth_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE for the base depth.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.base_node_id
    IS 'NODE IDENTIFIER: Unique identification number assigned to a specific point (node) on the wellbore.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.base_strat_name_set_id
    IS 'BASE STRATIGRAPHIC NAME SET ID: Name set from which the base stratigraphic unit is derived.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.base_strat_unit_id
    IS 'BASE STRAT UNIT ID: The stratigraphic unit (formation) identified as the base of the interval for a well component.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.bottom_hole_latitude
    IS 'BOTTOM HOLE LATITUDE: Latitude of bottom hole point projected to surface. For straight wells this would be exactly the same as surface latitude or null (denormalized form well_node).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.bottom_hole_longitude
    IS 'BOTTOM HOLE LONGITUDE: Longitude of bottom hole point projected to surface. For straight wells this would be exactly the same as surface longitude or null (denormalized form well_node).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.casing_flange_elev
    IS 'CASING FLANGE ELEVATION: Elevation of the casing flange measured from sea level.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.casing_flange_elev_ouom
    IS 'CASING FLANGE ELEVATION OUOM: Casing flange elevation original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.completion_date
    IS 'COMPLETION DATE: Date on the official filing or completion report indicating the well is established as ready to produce, inject or abandon.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confidential_date
    IS 'CONFIDENTIAL DATE: Date confidential information can be released to the general public.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confidential_depth
    IS 'CONFIDENTIAL DEPTH: Depth where a confidential formation begins.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confidential_depth_ouom
    IS 'CONFIDENTIAL DEPTH OUOM: Confidentiality depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confidential_type
    IS 'CONFEDENTIALITY TYPE: Describes the types of confidentiality types usually associated with a well. For example confidential, non-confidential or confidential 90 days.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confid_strat_name_set_id
    IS 'CONFIDENTIAL STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.confid_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.current_class
    IS 'WELL CLASS: REFERENCE WELL CLASSIFICATION: Identifies the classification of a well commonly based on the Lahee system. For example New Field Wildcat, Deeper Pool Test, Outpost or Development.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.current_status
    IS 'CURRENT STATUS: The present status, denormalized from the status table. Use only if needed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.current_status_date
    IS 'CURRENT STATUS DATE: Date of the current status of the well.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.deepest_depth
    IS 'WELL DEEPEST DEPTH: The deepest depth drilled occurs for remedial operations in which the new remedial depth is less than the original measured depth. The deepest depth captures the original measured depth before the remedial drilling event. The depth at time of completion is the remedial drilled depth. Deepest depth drilled allows the database to store any depths greater than the completed remedial depth.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.deepest_depth_ouom
    IS 'DEEPEST DEPTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.depth_datum
    IS 'DEPTH DATUM: The point from which all depths are measured. For example: kelly bushing, ground level, barge floor';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.depth_datum_elev
    IS 'DEPTH DATUM ELEVATION: Operator reported elevation of the measurement datum used as a reference for other measured well points.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.depth_datum_elev_ouom
    IS 'DEPTH DATUM ELEVATION OUOM: Depth Datum Elevation original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.derrick_floor_elev
    IS 'DERRICK FLOOR ELEVATION: Elevations that are reported from the Derrick floor.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.derrick_floor_elev_ouom
    IS 'DERRICK FLOOR ELEVATION ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.difference_lat_msl
    IS 'DIFFERENCE LOWEST ASTRONOMICAL TIDE MINUS MEAN SEA LEVEL: the computed difference between LAT and MSL.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.discovery_ind
    IS 'DISCOVERY INDICATOR: Y(es) or N(o) indicating the well is a discovery, a new, untapped oil/gas reservoir that has the potential to be economically feasible.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.drill_td
    IS 'DRILLERS TOTAL DEPTH: Total or maximum depth of the well as reported by the operator/ driller.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.drill_td_ouom
    IS 'DRILLERS TOTAL DEPTH OUOM: Driller total depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.effective_date
    IS 'EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.elev_ref_datum
    IS 'ELEVATION REFERENCE DATUM: the name of the datum to which elevations are referenced e.g. MSL or LAT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.environment_type
    IS 'ENVIRONMENT: the type of environment that the well is in, such as land, marine, transition zone etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.expiry_date
    IS 'EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.faulted_ind
    IS 'FAULTED INDICATOR: Y(es) or N(o) indicating a well has been faulted.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.final_drill_date
    IS 'FINAL DRILL DATE: Date the drilling operations for the well were finalized.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.final_td
    IS 'FINAL TOTAL DEPTH: The actual measurement along the well path from the reference datum to the bottom of the well.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.final_td_ouom
    IS 'FINAL TOTAL DEPTH OUOM: Final total depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.ground_elev
    IS 'GROUND ELEVEVATION: The elevation of the ground at the well site.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.ground_elev_ouom
    IS 'GROUND ELEVATION OUOM: Ground elevation original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.ground_elev_type
    IS 'GROUND ELEVATION TYPE: The type of point or horizontal surface used as an elevation reference for measurements in a well. For example: kelly bushing, ground, sea level.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.initial_class
    IS 'WELL CLASS: REFERENCE WELL CLASSIFICATION: Identifies the classification of a well commonly based on the Lahee system. For example New Field Wildcat, Deeper Pool Test, Outpost or Development';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.kb_elev
    IS 'KELLY BUSHING ELEVATION: The elevation of the kelly bushing (generally measured from sea level)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.kb_elev_ouom
    IS 'KELLY BUSHING ELEVATION OUOM: Kelly Bushing elevation original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.lease_name
    IS 'LEASE NAME: Name assigned to the lease by the regulatory agency with jurisdiction over the minerals in the area where the lease is located.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.lease_num
    IS 'LEASE NUMBER: Number assigned to the lease by the regulatory agency with jurisdiction over the minerals in the area where the lease is located.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.legal_survey_type
    IS 'LEGAL SURVEY TYPE: The survey type used for legal descriptions. For example, Carter, Congressional, Dominion Land Survey, ...';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.location_type
    IS 'LOCATION TYPE: Identifies the type of object being given a legal location. For example, node, well, ...';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.log_td
    IS 'LOGGERS TOTAL DEPTH: Total or maximum depth of the well as measured by the logging tool and reported by the logger/logging service.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.log_td_ouom
    IS 'LOGGERS TOTAL DEPTH OUOM: Logger total depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.max_tvd
    IS 'MAXIMUM TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH: The maximum true vertical depth from the surface datum reference to the final total depth or deepest point, measured on a straight line.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.max_tvd_ouom
    IS 'MAXIMUM TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH OUOM: Maximum true vertical depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.net_pay
    IS 'NET PAY: The cumulative reservoir rock capable of producing within the entire thickness of a pay zone. The net pay within a gross interval.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.net_pay_ouom
    IS 'NETPAY OUOM: Net pay original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.oldest_strat_age
    IS 'OLDEST STRATIGRAPHIC AGE: the name of the geologic age, such as Triassic, Jurassic, Quaternary Pleistocene, Tertiary Pliocene. The value will not be absolute geologic age in millions of years (125,000 mya).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.oldest_strat_name_set_age
    IS 'STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.oldest_strat_name_set_id
    IS 'OLDEST STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.oldest_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.operator
    IS 'OPERATOR: The Business Associate representing the owners of the well, responsible for the operations of drilling and producing the well and for reporting these activities to the partners and regulatory agencies.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.platform_id
    IS 'PLATFORM IDENTIFIER: Unique number assigned to the offshore drilling platform or onshore drilling pad..';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.platform_sf_subtype
    IS 'PLATFORM SF SUBTYPE: Part of the FK from SF PLATFORM.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.plot_name
    IS 'PLOT NAME: Well name alias used when plotting the well on a map.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.plot_symbol
    IS 'PLOT SYMBOL: A character or symbol used to represent well status. This may be a particular mapping package coding scheme, or a pointer to other application dependent files.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.plugback_depth
    IS 'PLUGBACK DEPTH: Depth of the point that the well was plugged back to when setting the casing or completing the well.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.plugback_depth_ouom
    IS 'PLUGBACK DEPTH OUOM: Plugback depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.ppdm_guid
    IS 'ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global unique identifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used, optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the data model DDL should be created.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.primary_source
    IS 'PRIMARY SOURCE: The primary source that was used to construct this well data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.profile_type
    IS 'WELLBORE SHAPE: A reference table describing a type of wellbore shape. For example vertical, horizontal, directional or s-shaped.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.regulatory_agency
    IS 'BUSINESS ASSOCIATE: Unique identifier for a business associate, such as a person, company, regulatory agency, government or consortium.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.remark
    IS 'REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.rig_on_site_date
    IS 'RIG ON SITE DATE: The date that the drilling rig is moved onto the well site.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.rig_release_date
    IS 'RIG RELEASE DATE: Date the drilling rig can be released from operations and moved from the well site as specified in the contract.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.rotary_table_elev
    IS 'ROTARY TABLE ELEV: The elevation of the rotary table. This is needed to track Australian information.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.rotary_table_elev_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.source_document_id
    IS 'SOURCE DOCUMENT: A list of documents that are used as the source for supplying data. Source documents may include government and regulatory forms, operator reports or scout tickets, publications, news letters, books or journals.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.spud_date
    IS 'SPUD DATE: Date the drilling operations commenced on the well. The first day hole is made.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.status_type
    IS 'STATUS TYPE: The type of status reported for the well. Can include construction status, operating status, producing status, abandonment status etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.subsea_elev_ref_type
    IS 'SUBSEA REFERENCE ELEVATION TYPE: The reported type of elevation that was used to determine the subsea elevation, such as Kelly Bushing, Driller Floor, Casing Flange, Rotary Table etc. The Subsea elevation is computed by subtracting the ground elevation from the elevation reported by the drilling contractor.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.surface_latitude
    IS 'SURFACE LATITUDE: Angular distance in decimal degrees, north or south of the equator. A positive value represents a north latitude. (denormalized from the well node table)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.surface_longitude
    IS 'SURFACE LONGITUDE: Angular distance in decimal degrees, east or west of the prime meridian of the geodetic datum. A negative value represents a west longitude. (denormalized from the well node table)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.surface_node_id
    IS 'NODE IDENTIFIER: Unique identification number assigned to a specific point (node) on the wellbore.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.tax_credit_code
    IS 'TAX CREDIT CODE: Code indicating the well qualifies for a tax credit. "C" = credit for the well being permitted for coalbed methane gas.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.td_strat_age
    IS 'TOTAL DEPTH STRATIGRAPHIC AGE: the name of the geologic age, such as Triassic, Jurassic, Quaternary Pleistocene, Tertiary Pliocene. The value will not be absolute geologic age in millions of years (125,000 mya) .';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.td_strat_name_set_age
    IS 'TOTAL DEPTH STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the AGE BASED stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.td_strat_name_set_id
    IS 'TOTAL DEPTH STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.td_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.top_depth
    IS 'TOP DEPTH: the shallowest or top measured depth in which this well component is found.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.top_depth_ouom
    IS 'TOP DEPTH ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.top_strat_name_set_id
    IS 'TOP STRATIGRAPHIC NAME SET ID: Name set from which the top stratigraphic unit is derived.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.top_strat_unit_id
    IS 'TOP STRAT UNIT ID: The stratigraphic unit (formation) identified as the top of the interval for a well component.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.water_acoustic_vel
    IS 'WATER ACOUSTIC VELOCITY: the average acoustic velocity from surface to sea bed near the well site.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.water_acoustic_vel_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.water_depth
    IS 'WATER DEPTH: Depth of the water at a well (measured from the water level to the mud line).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.water_depth_datum
    IS 'WATER DATUM: Reference datum to which the water depth is referenced, such as mean sea level.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.water_depth_ouom
    IS 'WATER DEPTH OUOM: Water depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_event_num
    IS 'WELL EVENT NUMBER: Allows well events such as re-entries to be tracked separately, rather than embedded as a component in the UWI.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_government_id
    IS 'WELL GOVERNMENT IDENTIFIER: Number assigned by a regulatory agency or government to identify a well. For example API or CPA number.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_intersect_md
    IS 'WELL INTERSECT MEASURED DEPTH: The measured depth of the point of intersection of the parent well and this well. Also referred to as kick-off point.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_level_type
    IS 'WELL LEVEL TYPE: Indicates which well component this row describes, as outlined in www.WhatIsAWell.org. Values may include WELL, WELL ORIGIN, WELLBORE, WELLBORE SEGMENT, WELLBORE COMPLETION or WELLBORE CONTACT INTERVAL. UNKNOWN may be used if the type of component is not known. Well Sets should be loaded into WELL_SET. WELLHEAD STREAM is mapped into FACILITY.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_name
    IS 'WELL NAME: Name assigned to the well. This may be the legal or registered name as it appears on a permit or a given name assigned by the operator.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.well_num
    IS 'WELL NUMBER: Number or alphanumeric name assigned to each well by the operator. For example J21 or 10-26.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.whipstock_depth
    IS 'WHIPSTOCK DEPTH: Measurement of the depth position of the whipstock. This is used for side tracking or directional drilling.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.whipstock_depth_ouom
    IS 'WHIPSTOCK DEPTH OUOM: Whipstock depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_changed_by
    IS 'ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_changed_date
    IS 'ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_created_by
    IS 'ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_created_date
    IS 'ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_effective_date
    IS 'ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was made available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_expiry_date
    IS 'ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is no longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was no longer available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well.row_quality
    IS 'PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row, usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, although other types of quality reference are permitted.';

