COMMENT ON TABLE ppdm.well_dir_srvy
    IS 'WELL DIRECTIONAL SURVEY: The Well Directional Survey table contains header information about directional surveys which have  been performed on a wellbore. This downhole survey charts the  degree of departure of the wellbore from vertical and the direction of departure. Since many directional surveys can be conducted on  a wellbore, the survey number is included as part of the primary key to uniquely identify the survey.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.uwi
    IS 'UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as the primary key for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_id
    IS 'DIRECTIONAL SURVEY IDENTIFIER: Number uniquely identifying each Directional Survey.  Assign as a unique value (for example a sequence number) for either 1) unique to each given UWI and SOURCE, 2) unique to each UWI, regardless of SOURCE, or 3) unique to each WELL_DIR_SRVY record, regardless of UWI and/or SOURCE.  This attribute should not be used to store or have any relation to "Run Numbers" (SURVEY_RUN_NUM) or "Reference numbers/identifiers/etc." (SURVEY_REF_NUM) associated with a given survey because it is part of the table Primary Key.  If it were used to store "Run Numbers" or "Reference numbers/identifiers/etc.", then it would not be possible to store two versions of a given survey having the same "Run Number" or "Reference number/identifier/etc." (for example, two different X/Y Offset calculation methods).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.source
    IS 'SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as the source of information for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.active_ind
    IS 'ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently active or valid.   If a given WELL_DIR_SRVY records is identified as Inactive (i.e. WELL_DIR_SRVY.ACTIVE_IND=''N''), then the survey stations in WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION corresponding to the same UWI, SURVEY_ID and SOURCE are by default also implied/assumed to be Inactive, regardless of the value assigned to their WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.ACTIVE_IND.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_coord_sys_id
    IS 'AZIMUTH COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: Coordinate Reference System ID that best identifies the CRS of the WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.AZIMUTH values.  Use to idenfity Geodetic Datum if North Reference (AZIMUTH_NORTH_TYPE) is True; an appropriate Cartesian CRS ID for Grid North Reference; leave NULL for Magnetic North Reference.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_coord_sys_qualifier
    IS 'AZIMUTH COORDINATE SYSTEM QUALIFIER: Qualifier assigning an appropriate level of confidence of the reliability of the value stored in AZIMUTH_COORD_SYSTEM_ID, such as VERIFIED, STATED, INFERRED, ASSUMED, UNKNOWN, etc.  For example, if the CRS is clearly, completely and accurately defined in the Directional Survey header, and can be verified as being correct, assign ''VERIFIED''.  If, however, the some of all of the CRS information is not explicitly stated, but can be assumed based on other information such as other surveys performed during the same time frame in the same area by the same survey aquisition company, a qualifier such as ''ASSUMED'' might be more accurate.  Refer to the descriptions of specific values in the corresponding reference table.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_coord_sys_remark
    IS 'AZIMUTH COORDINATE SYSTEM REMARK: Remarks about Azimuth Coordinate Reference System.  Since the key components of the CRS (Datum, Type, Zone and UOM) are usually NOT well defined or are only partially defined in directional survey report or header, use this attribute to identify these key components, along with descriptions whether each is Correctly Stated, Inferred from other information, Assumed, Unknown, etc.  Examples of these key components incude: Datum (NAD27, NAD83, WGS84, ...), Type (Lambert, UTM, ...), Zone (1702, 14, ...) and Units of Measure (Feet, Meters).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_corr_angle
    IS 'AZIMUTH CORRECTION ANGLE: Correction Angle that was ADDED to prior Azimuths (RPT_AZIMUTH) to correct them to the stored AZIMUTH, stored as a positive or negative value with NO corresponding E/W Direction indicator attribute.  For example, if the stored Azimuth (AZIMUTH) values are referenced to True North and the reported Azimuth (RPT_AZIMUTH) values are referenced to Grid North, the formula used to correct the reported values is: RPT_AZIMUTH + AZIMUTH_CORR_ANGLE = AZIMUTH (conversely, to determine the reported values: AZIMUTH - AZIMUTH_CORR_ANGLE = RPT_AZIMUTH).  In this example, the AZIMUTH_CORR_ANGLE_TYPE would be set to the code describing a "Grid-to-True" correction angle.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_corr_angle_ouom
    IS 'AZIMUTH CORRECTION ANGLE OUOM: Azimuth correction angle original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_corr_angle_type
    IS 'AZIMUTH CORRECTION ANGLE TYPE: Defines the type of correction angle used to correct the prior Azimuth (RPT_AZIMUTH) values to the stored AZIMUTH values (i.e. Grid-to-True, Magnetic-to-Grid, etc.).  Applies to the AZIMUTH_CORR_ANGLE field.  Set to "NONE" if NO correction was applied.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.azimuth_north_type
    IS 'AZIMUTH NORTH TYPE: The North reference used to define AZIMUTH angular measurement values stored in WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION for this Directional Survey (UWI, SURVEY_ID, SOURCE).  For example, True North, Grid North, Magnetic North, etc. Include Qualifier in the value - e.g. ''TRUE'' vs. ''INFERRED TRUE'' vs. ''ASSUME TRUE''.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.base_depth
    IS 'SURVEY BASE DEPTH: Measured depth in borehole of the LAST surveyed station.  If a stored survey has been extrapolated to a deeper depth than the last surveyed station, enter the deepest extrapolated measured depth in EXTRAPOLATE_DEPTH.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.base_depth_ouom
    IS 'SURVEY BASE OUOM: Survey base depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.compute_method
    IS 'COMPUTE METHOD: Calculation Method used to compute theWELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION TVD, X_OFFSET, Y_OFFSET and DOG_LEG_SEVERITY values for this Directional Survey (UWI, SURVEY_ID, SOURCE). For example, Radius of Curvature, Minimum Curvature, Balanced Tangential, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.confidential_type
    IS 'CONFIDENTIAL TYPE: Describes the type of confidentiality of this survey. For example TIGHT, OPEN, etc. The Directional Survey confidentiality my differ from the general WELL confidentiality.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.coord_acquisition_id
    IS 'COORDINATE ACQUISITION ID: Identifies an assembly of coordinate data that must be grouped together.  The coordinate data should be acquired together at the same time, from the same source, using the same method (theoretical, metes and bounds, paced off, GPS, scanned from base map, etc.) and at the same accuracy.  May be used to indicate the level of accuracy of a set of coordinates.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.dir_survey_class
    IS 'DIRECTIONAL SURVEY CLASS: Class of this directional survey.  For example, "Directional Survey" (where MD, Inclination and Azimuth are all measured) vs. "Position Log" (where Inclination and Azimuth are both null and only MD, TVD and X/Y Offsets are available).  This attribute may also be used to identify "PROPOSED" or "PLANNED" surveys.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.effective_date
    IS 'EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.expiry_date
    IS 'EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.extrapolate_depth
    IS 'EXTRAPOLATE DEPTH: The depth to which the segment was extrapolated.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.extrapolate_depth_ouom
    IS 'EXTRAPOLATE DEPTH OUOM: Extrapolate depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.extrapolate_ind
    IS 'EXTRAPOLATE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag to indicate if extrapolation to a non-surveyed depth occurred. Only applicable to CALCULATED surveys.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.geog_coord_sys_id
    IS 'LATITUDE/LONGITUDE COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: Coordinate Reference System ID defining the Geodetic Datum of the WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION LATITUDE and LONGITUDE values.  If LATITUDE and LONGITUDE attributes in WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION are stored, clearly identifying thier Datum is required.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.local_coord_sys_id
    IS 'LOCAL COORDINATE SYSTEM IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the local coordinate system, such as a local grid system (ATS, STS, MTS etc) to which these coordinates have been referenced.  Relevant in places where the legal survey location is referenced to a physical marker (like a survey pin) located in a physical place (such as the NE Corner of a section).  In places where the mapping system is not exactly synchronized with the real ground coordinates, it''s important to understand which local reference system references are made to.  Coordinates that are referenced to a local coordinate system are usually surveyed relative to the local system using metes and bounds or local survey references; maintaining the position of each point relative to its referenced local system is very important to survey accuracy.  Also, some local coordinate systems may change over time, so it is critical to keep track of which local coordinate system was used at the time the survey was acquired.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.magnetic_declination
    IS 'MAGNETIC DECLINATION: Value for the declination angle measured FROM True north TO the Magnetic referenced north at the survey location.   This value can be stored in one of two methods - 1) Store as a positive/negative number and ignore MAGNETIC_DECLINATION_EW_DIR, or 2) Store as an absolute value number and use MAGNETIC_DECLINATION_EW_DIR to identify if the value is positive (E) or negative (W).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.magnetic_declination_ouom
    IS 'MAGNETIC DECLINATION OUOM: Magnetic Declination angle original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.mag_decl_ew_direction
    IS 'MAGNETIC DECLINATION EAST-WEST DIRECTION: East-West direction indicator for MAGNETIC_DECLINATION angle.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.offset_coord_sys_id
    IS 'OFFSET COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: Coordinate Reference System ID that best identifies the CRS of the WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION X_OFFSET, Y_OFFSET, CLOSURE_DIST and VERTICAL_SECTION values.  Use to idenfity Geodetic Datum if North Reference (OFFSET_NORTH_TYPE) is True; an appropriate Cartesian CRS ID for Grid North Reference; leave NULL for Magnetic North Reference. The Coordinate Reference System. for the Offsets CAN BE different from the AZIMUTH Coordinate Reference System.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.offset_coord_sys_qualifier
    IS 'OFFSET COORDINATE SYS QUALIFIER: Qualifier assigning an appropriate level of confidence of the reliability of the value stored in OFFSET_COORD_SYSTEM_ID, such as VERIFIED, STATED, INFERRED, ASSUMED, UNKNOWN, etc.  Refer to the AZIMUTH_COORD_SYS_QUALIFIER Column Comments for additional details.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.offset_coord_sys_remark
    IS 'OFFSET COORDINATE SYSYEM REMARK: Remarks about Offset Coordinate Reference System.  Refer to the AZIMUTH_COORD_SYS_REMARK Column Comments for additional details.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.offset_north_type
    IS 'OFFSET NORTH TYPE: The North reference of the WELL_DIR_SRVY PLANE_OF_PROPOSAL and WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION X_OFFSET, Y_OFFSET, CLOSURE_DIST_DIR and VERTICAL_SECTION values for this Directional Survey (UWI, SURVEY_ID, SOURCE).  For example, True North, Grid North, etc. Include Qualifier in the value - e.g. ''TRUE'' vs. ''INFERRED TRUE'' vs. ''ASSUME TRUE''.  The North Reference for the Offsets CAN BE different from the AZIMUTH North Reference.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.plane_of_proposal
    IS 'PLANE OF PROPOSAL: The direction angle of a horizontal line from the survey origin (Well surface location) to the planned or intended target.  This value should be a number between 0.00 and 360.00 degrees; 0.00 and 360.00 represent North, 90.00 is East, 180.00 is South and 270.00 is West.  The Plane of Proposal angle North Reference is defined by WELL_DIR_SRVY.OFFSET_NORTH_TYPE and CRS by WELL_DIR_SRVY.OFFSET_COORD_SYSTEM_ID.  This attribute is used in the calculations for WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.VERTICAL_SECTION.  Also often referred to as: "Vertical Section Direction", "Vertical Section Azimuth", "Proposed Bottomhole Location (PBHL)", or "Target Direction".  Since PLANE_OF_PROPOSAL is an azimuth number between 0.00 and 360.00 degrees, there is no need for a corresponding PLANE_OF_PROPOSAL_EW_DIR attribute.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.plane_of_proposal_ouom
    IS 'PLANE OF PROPOSAL OUOM: Plane of proposal original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.ppdm_guid
    IS 'ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global unique identifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used, optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the data model DDL should be created.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.preferred_ind
    IS 'PREFERRED INDICATOR:  A Y/N flag indicating whether this survey is the preferred Directional Survey for the UWI.  Only one row per UWI should have the PREFERRED_IND flag set to "Y", All other surveys for the same UWI should have PREFERRED_IND set to "N".   Raw, unprocessed surveys should not have PREFERRED_IND set to "Y".';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rad_uncert_dist
    IS 'RADIUS OF UNCERTAINTY DISTANCE: The radius of uncertainty distance of the bottom hole location caused primarily by sections of the wellbore where only inclination data exists.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rad_uncert_dist_ouom
    IS 'RADIUS OF UNCERTAINTY DISTANCE OUOM: Radius of Uncertainty Distance original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rad_uncert_dist_reason
    IS 'RADIUS OF UNCERTAINTY DISTANCE REASON: Reason for Radius of Uncertainty.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.record_mode
    IS 'RECORD MODE: Record Mode for this Directional Survey.  For example, multi shot, single shot, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.remark
    IS 'REMARK: Remarks pertaining to the directional survey operations.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_apd
    IS 'REPORTED HEIGHT ABOVE PERMANENT DATUM: The height of the log datum Above the reported Permanent Datum (APD), as reported by the source of this row. Reference APD in LAS format. To adjust a reported depth to the reported permanent datum, compute e.g. LOG DATUM ELEV - PERMANENT DATUM ELEV.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_log_datum
    IS 'REPORTED LOG DATUM: The datum from which the log depths are measured. The point at which log depth equals zero, e.g. kelly bushing. Reference DREF in LAS format.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_log_datum_elev
    IS 'REPORTED LOG DATUM ELEVATION: The elevation of the LOG_DATUM, as reported by the source of this row. Reference EREF in LAS format.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_log_datum_elev_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_perm_datum
    IS 'REPORTED PERMANENT DATUM: The permanent datum as reported by the source of this row. Reference PDAT in LAS format. Generally, this value should be the same as WELL.DEPTH_DATUM, but in rare cases it may be different.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_perm_datum_elev
    IS 'REPORTED PERMANENT DATUM ELEVATION: The reported elevation of the permanent datum. This should be the same as WELL.DEPTH_DATUM_ELEV, but in rare cases it may be different. Reference EPD in LAS.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.report_perm_datum_elev_ouom
    IS 'REPORTED PERMANENT DATUM ELEVATION ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE:';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.resample_interval
    IS 'RESAMPLE INTERVAL: A re-sampling of original hardcopy or digital data to reduce certain types of surveys that have an excessive number of points or where the station intervals are too small. Normally only used with dipmeter data or other interpolated surveys where station spacing ranges from 1-20 ft.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.resample_interval_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE for this row of data';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_coord_sys_id
    IS 'REPORT COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: Coordinate Reference System ID that best identifies the CRS of the WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.RPT_AZIMUTH values.  Use to idenfity Geodetic Datum if North Reference (RPT_NORTH_TYPE) is True; an appropriate Cartesian CRS ID for Grid North Reference; leave NULL for Magnetic North Reference.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_coord_sys_qualifier
    IS 'REPORT COORDINATE SYSTEM QUALIFIER: Qualifier assigning an appropriate level of confidence of the reliability of the value stored in RPT_COORD_SYSTEM_ID, such as VERIFIED, STATED, INFERRED, ASSUMED, UNKNOWN, etc.  Refer to the AZIMUTH_COORD_SYS_QUALIFIER Column Comments for additional details.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_coord_sys_remark
    IS 'REPORT COORDINATE SYSTEM REMARK: Remarks about RPT_AZIMUTH Coordinate Reference System.  Refer to the AZIMUTH_COORD_SYS_REMARK Column Comments for additional details.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_corr_angle
    IS 'REPORT CORRECTION ANGLE: Report Correction Angle, as defined in the Directional Survey Report, hardcopy, PDF, etc.; stored as a positive or negative value with NO corresponding E/W Direction indicator attribute.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_corr_angle_ouom
    IS 'REPORT CORRECTION ANGLE OUOM: Report correction angle original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_corr_angle_type
    IS 'REPORT CORRECTION ANGLE TYPE: Defines the type of Report Correction Angle (i.e. Grid-to-True, Magnetic-to-Grid, etc.).  Applies to the RPT_CORR_ANGLE field.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_north_type
    IS 'REPORT NORTH TYPE: The North reference used to define RPT_AZIMUTH angular measurement values stored in WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION for this Directional Survey (UWI, SURVEY_ID, SOURCE).  For example, True North, Grid North, Magnetic North, etc. Include Qualifier in the value - e.g. ''TRUE'' vs. ''INFERRED TRUE'' vs. ''ASSUME TRUE''.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_survey_type
    IS 'REPORT SURVEY TYPE:  Type of Tool or Equipment used to acquire the Reported (raw, original) Directional Survey; For example, gyroscopic, magnetic, MWD, totco, acid bottle, etc. Only applicable for RAW surveys.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_azimuth
    IS 'REPORT TIE AZIMUTH: The UNPROCESSED or Original azimuth at the measured depth of a tie point.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_azimuth_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE AZIMUTH OUOM: Report tie azimuth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_inclination
    IS 'REPORT TIE INCLINATION: The inclination at the measured depth of a tie point.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_inclination_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE INCLINATION OUOM: Report tie inclination original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_md
    IS 'REPORT TIE MD: Tie-point Depth measured along the borehole from the Measurement Reference Datum to the survey station.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_md_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE MD OUOM: Report tie measued depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_point_ind
    IS 'REPORT TIE POINT INDICATOR: A Y/N Flag indicating the the Tie-Point is required to exist for this survey.  Set to ''Y'' if a Tie-Point is required, set to ''N'' if NO Tie-Point is required, or leave NULL if Tie-Point requirement is unknown.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_tvd
    IS 'REPORT TIE TVD: The true vertical depth at the measured depth tie point of a referenced tie.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_tvd_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE TVD OUOM: Report tie true vertical depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_x_offset
    IS 'REPORT TIE X OFFSET: The initial east/west offset distance of a directional survey where some or all of the interval above the first survey point is missing. This value can be stored in one of two methods - 1) Store as a positive/negative number and ignore the corresponding RPT_TIE_X_OFFSET_EW_DIR or 2) Store as an absolute value number and use RPT_TIE_X_OFFSET_EW_DIR to identify if the value is positive (E) or negative (W).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_x_offset_ew_dir
    IS 'REPORT TIE X OFFSET EAST-WEST DIRECTION: Direction (East or West) of the RPT_TIE_X_OFFSET';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_x_offset_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE X OFFSET OUOM: Report tie X offset original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_y_offset
    IS 'REPORT TIE Y OFFSET: The initial north/south offset distance of a directional survey where some or all of the interval above the first survey point is missing. This value can be stored in one of two methods - 1) Store as a positive/negative number and ignore the corresponding RPT_TIE_Y_OFFSET_NS_DIR or 2) Store as an absolute value number and use RPT_TIE_Y_OFFSET_NS_DIR to identify if the value is positive (N) or negative (S).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_y_offset_ns_dir
    IS 'REPORT TIE Y OFFSET NORTH-SOUTH DIRECTION: Direction (North or South) of the RPT_TIE_Y_OFFSET';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.rpt_tie_y_offset_ouom
    IS 'REPORT TIE Y OFFSET OUOM: Report tie Y offset original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.source_document_id
    IS 'SOURCE DOCUMENT: A list of documents that are used as the source for supplying data. Source documents may include government and regulatory forms, operator reports or scout tickets, publications, news letters, books or jounals.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_company_ba_id
    IS 'SURVEY COMPANY BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: BUSINESS_ASSOCIATE code identifying the individual, company, agency or source that ACQUIRED this survey data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_compiler_ba_id
    IS 'SURVEY COMPILER BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: BUSINESS_ASSOCIATE code identifying the company compiling the survey report. May be same as SURVEY_COMPANY_BA_ID if the company who Aqcuired the data also Compiled it, but if a different company Compiled data originally Acquired by one or more other companies, then this value would be different from SURVEY_COMPANY_BA_ID.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_digital_prvdr_ba_id
    IS 'SURVEY DIGITAL PROVIDER BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: BUSINESS_ASSOCIATE code identifying the individual, company, agency or source that provided the survey data in a digital form.  This may or may not be the same as the company who acquired the data, compiled the data, or  provided a report (hard-copy, PDF, etc.) of the survey.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_end_date
    IS 'SURVEY END DATE: Date the directional survey was conducted if the survey was started and finished the same day, else the date that the survey was completed.  SURVEY_START_DATE must be Equal to or Earlier than SURVEY_END_DATE.  Recommended that both SURVEY_START_DATE and SURVEY_END_DATE are populated, even if they are the same.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_end_date_qualifier
    IS 'SURVEY END DATE QUALIFIER: Qualifier assigning an appropriate level of confidence of the reliability of the Survey End Date (SURVEY_END_DATE), such as VERIFIED, STATED, INFERRED, ASSUMED, UNKNOWN, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_process_method
    IS 'SURVEY PROCESS METHOD: The processing method of the reported (original hardcopy, PDF, etc.) data: interpolated, non-interpolated or mixed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_quality
    IS 'SURVEY QUALITY: Subjective qualifier for the quality of the directional survey.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_ref_num
    IS 'SURVEY REFERENCE NUMBER: Unique or Distinctive Survey Reference Number, Job Number, File Number, Identifier, Label, Name, etc. as indicated on a directional survey report, file, etc.  Use this attribute to allow correlation of the data in this Directional Survey back to the original source document, file, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_report_type
    IS 'SURVEY REPORT TYPE: The type of report for this survey.  Use this to identify an individual survey run (RUN); a survey containing multiple runs combined together (COMBINED RUN); or a survey that has been re-processed, corrected, validated and composited from either a single or multiple runs (COMPOSITE).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_run_num
    IS 'SURVEY RUN NUMBER: Survey Run Number, null in WELL_DIR_SRVY if multiple runs are combined/composited.  Run number is typically NOT explicitly stated on a given directional survey report, but is often assigned when multiple survey runs are evaluated, processes and/or composited.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_start_date
    IS 'SURVEY START DATE: Date the directional survey was conducted if the survey was started and finished the same day, else the date that the survey was Started.  SURVEY_START_DATE must be Equal to or Earlier than SURVEY_END_DATE.  Recommended that both SURVEY_START_DATE and SURVEY_END_DATE are populated, even if they are the same.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_start_date_qualifier
    IS 'SURVEY START DATE QUALIFIER: Qualifier assigning an appropriate level of confidence of the reliability of the Survey Start Date (SURVEY_START_DATE), such as VERIFIED, STATED, INFERRED, ASSUMED, UNKNOWN, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.survey_type
    IS 'SURVEY TYPE: Type of Tool or Equipment used to acquire this Directional Survey.  For example, gyroscopic, magnetic, MWD, totco, acid bottle, etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.top_depth
    IS 'SURVEY TOP DEPTH: Measured depth in wellbore where the directional survey starts.  This value should equal the Minimum WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.MD for this Directional Survey (UWI, SURVEY_ID, SOURCE), regardless of whether the Minimum WELL_DIR_SRVY_STATION.MD represents an actual surveyed MD or not.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.top_depth_ouom
    IS 'SURVEY TOP OUOM: Survey top depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_changed_by
    IS 'ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_changed_date
    IS 'ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_created_by
    IS 'ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_created_date
    IS 'ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_effective_date
    IS 'ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was made available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_dir_srvy.row_expiry_date
