COMMENT ON TABLE ppdm.well_test
    IS 'WELL TEST: The Well Test table contains descriptive information concerning a test date, depth interval, the objective stratigraphic unit, and other general data for a DST (Drill Stem Test) and productivity test. These tests are used as an evaluation tool to help determine the potential of the reservoir without completing the well.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.uwi
    IS 'UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as the primary key for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.source
    IS 'SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as the source of information for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.test_type
    IS 'WELL TEST TYPE: Identifies the general type of test used to evaluate the potential of the well. For example, Drill Stem Tests (DST), Repeat Formation Tests (RFT), Initial Potential(IP).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.run_num
    IS 'RUN NUMBER: A number which uniquely identifies the run or trip into the well for the purpose of operating a test';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.test_num
    IS 'TEST_NUMBER: A number used to uniquely identify the individual test occurring within a test run or trip.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.active_ind
    IS 'ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently either active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.base_depth
    IS 'BASE DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the base of the test interval.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.base_depth_ouom
    IS 'BASE DEPTH OUOM: Base measured depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.base_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.bhp_z
    IS 'BOTTOM HOLE PRESSURE / Z: Value for the amount of bottom hole pressure measured over the compressibility (Z) factor. This is a derived value and should be populated programmatically.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.bottom_choke_desc
    IS 'BOTTOM CHOKE DESCRIPTION: A description of the bottom choke diameter (e.g., 1 1/2 inches).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.bsw_percent
    IS 'BASIC SEDIMENT and WATER PERCENTAGE: The percentage of basic sediment and water. The solid impurities and salt water that are mixed with crude oil. This is the same as bottom settlings and water.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.caliper_hole_diameter
    IS 'CALINER HOLE DIAMETER: Value of the diameter of the borehole measured by a caliper instrument';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.caliper_hole_diameter_ouom
    IS 'CALINER HOLE DIAMETER OUOM: Caliper diameter original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.cased_hole_ind
    IS 'CASED HOLE INDICATOR: Identifies the formation test was performed in a cased hole environment.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.casing_pressure
    IS 'CASING PRESSURE: Value of the pressure measured between the casing and drillstring. Casing pressure is measured at the surface after the well has been shutin.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_test.casing_pressure_ouom
    IS 'CASING PRESSURE OUOM: Casing pressure original unit of measure.';

