COMMENT ON TABLE ppdm.well_tubular
    IS 'WELL TUBULAR: The Well Tubular table contains information on the tubulars for the well. The tubulars can be tubing, casing or liners which are run into the well. A tubing string is a continuous length of pipe used to connect the producing interval in the well tothe flowline at the surface. A casing string is a continuous length of pipe used to protect the walls of the well and to assist in interval isolation when completing the well. The table identifies each tubular stri ng used in a single drilling phase of the well. Liners are used to prevent sand from entering the well bore.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.uwi
    IS 'UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as the primary key for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.source
    IS 'SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as the source of information for this row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_type
    IS 'TUBING TYPE: This reference table describes the particular type of tubular or type. For example tubing, casing or liner. This is a general classification. A more specific description can be found in R_LINER_TYPE.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_obs_no
    IS 'TUBING OBSERVATION NUMBER: Number identifying, in sequence, each change in pipe size.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.active_ind
    IS 'ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently either active / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.base_depth
    IS 'BASE DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the base of the drilling pipe.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.base_depth_ouom
    IS 'BASE DEPTH OUOM: Base measured depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.base_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.cat_equip_id
    IS 'EQUIPMENT CATALOGUE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the list of kinds of equipment. Think of this as a catalogue or brochure that shows all the kinds of equipment that you may use, but may or may not actually have. Actual peices of equipment that exist are defined in the table EQUIPMENT.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.collar_type
    IS 'COLLAR TYPE: The type of collar used to couple the tubular with another tubing string.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.coupling_type
    IS 'COUPLING TYPE: A short length of pipe used to connect two joints of casing. A casing coupling has internal threads (female threadform) machined to match the external threads (male threadform) of the long joints of casing. The two joints of casing are threaded into opposite ends of the casing coupling. Synonyms: casing collar (Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.effective_date
    IS 'EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.equipment_id
    IS 'EQUIPMENT IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a specific peice of equipment.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.expiry_date
    IS 'EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.hole_size
    IS 'HOLE SIZE: Measurement of the diameter of the tubular hole.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.hole_size_ouom
    IS 'HOLE SIZE OUOM: Hole size original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.hung_top_depth
    IS 'HUNG TOP DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the top of the drilling pipe.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.hung_top_depth_ouom
    IS 'HUNG TOP OUOM: Hung top depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.inside_diameter
    IS 'INSIDE DIAMETER: Measurement of the inside diameter size of the tubular bore/pipe.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.inside_diameter_ouom
    IS 'INSIDE DIAMETER OUOM: Inside diameter original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.joint_count
    IS 'JOINT COUNT: Total number of joints in the string. A joint is a length of pipe, usually referring to drillpipe, casing or tubing. While there are different standard lengths, the most common drillpipe joint length is around 30 ft [9 m]. For casing, the most common length of a joint is 40 ft [12 m]. (schlumberger Oilfield Glossary).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.left_in_hole_length
    IS 'LEFT IN HOLE LENGTH: the amount of casing left in the hole after pulling operations have been performed, prior to plugging or remedial work.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.left_in_hole_length_ouom
    IS 'LEFT IN HOLE LENGTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.liner_type
    IS 'LINER TYPE: This reference table describes the type of liner used in the borehole. For example, slotted, gravel packed or pre-perforated et c.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.manufacturer_ba_id
    IS 'MANUIFACTURER: Unique identifier for the manufacturer of this equipment. Ideally, this information should be captured in the table CAT EQUIPMENT, making this column and other specificaiton columns redundant in this table.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.mixed_string_ind
    IS 'MIXED STRING INDICATOR: A Y( es) or N(o) flag indicating the casing is a mixed string. The length of the casing may be made up of joints with different tensile strengths, or collapse resistance and yield strengths.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.observation_date
    IS 'OBSERVATION DATE: Date the tubular observation occurred.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.outside_diameter
    IS 'OUTSIDE DIAMETER: Measurement of the outside diameter size of the tubular bore/pipe.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.outside_diameter_desc
    IS 'OUTSIDE DIAMETER DESCRIPTION: Description of the outside diameter of the tubular/pipe (e.g., 9 5/8).';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.outside_diameter_ouom
    IS 'OUTSIDE DIAMETER OUOM: Outside diameter original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.packer_set_depth
    IS 'PACKER SET DEPTH: The depth the packer equipment was set to seal the casing or tubing.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.packer_set_depth_ouom
    IS 'PACKER SET DEPTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.period_obs_no
    IS 'WELL DRILLING PERIOD OBSERVATION NUMBER: unique identifier for a reporting period for well operations. Internationally, there may be 1, 2 or 3 periods each 24 hours. In some jurisdictions, reporting may occur for more than one period, such as for an 8 hour tour shift and a 24 daily summary.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.ppdm_guid
    IS 'ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global unique identifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used, optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the data model DDL should be created.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.pulled_length
    IS 'PULLED LENGTH: the length of the portion of casing that is pulled from a well bore, primarily during plugging operations or remedial work.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.pulled_length_ouom
    IS 'PULLED LENGTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.remark
    IS 'REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.reported_base_tvd
    IS 'REPORTED TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH: The reported depth of a well measured vertically from the surface to the point of interest in the well bore. These reported values may not represent the actual TVD as derivable from the directional survey and may consequently be in error.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.reported_base_tvd_ouom
    IS 'REPORTED BASE TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE:';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.reported_top_tvd
    IS 'REPORTED TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH: The reported depth of a well measured vertically from the surface to the point of interest in the well bore. These reported values may not represent the actual TVD as derivable from the directional survey and may consequently be in error.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.reported_top_tvd_ouom
    IS 'REPORTED TOP TRUE VERTICAL DEPTH ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE:';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.sea_floor_penetration
    IS 'SEA FLOOR PENETRATION: the distance that the casing has penetrated below the surface of the sea floor.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.sea_floor_penetration_ouom
    IS 'SEA FLOOR PENETRATION ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.shoe_depth
    IS 'SHOE DEPTH: Depth of the tubing shoe measured from the surface.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.shoe_depth_ouom
    IS 'SHOE DEPTH OUOM: Shoe depth original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.steel_spec
    IS 'STEEL SPECIFICATION: Manufacture"s specification under which the steel was constructed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.strat_name_set_id
    IS 'STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. A stratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be in use for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.top_strat_unit_id
    IS 'STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.torque
    IS 'TORQUE: The torque applied to the joint between two components.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.torque_ouom
    IS 'ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_density
    IS 'TUBING DENSITY: Density measurement (mass per unit lenght) of the tubular.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_density_ouom
    IS 'DENSITY OUOM: Tubular density original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_grade
    IS 'TUBING GRADE: the tensile strength of the tubing material. A system of classifying the material specifications for steel alloys used in the manufacture of tubing.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_strength
    IS 'STRENGTH: The axial load required to yield the pipe.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_strength_ouom
    IS 'TUBING STRENGTH OUOM: Tubing strength original unit of measure.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_weight
    IS 'TUBING WEIGHT: Weight measurement of the tubular';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.tubing_weight_ouom
    IS 'TUBING WEIGHT ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE:';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_changed_by
    IS 'ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_changed_date
    IS 'ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_created_by
    IS 'ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_created_date
    IS 'ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_effective_date
    IS 'ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was made available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_expiry_date
    IS 'ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data is no longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data was no longer available to end users, for example.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN ppdm.well_tubular.row_quality
    IS 'PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row, usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, although other types of quality reference are permitted.';

